SS Sergeant Oskar Groening set to go on trial charged with complicity in the killing of 300,000 Jews at the Nazi extermination camp . 
  Auschwitz survivors and relatives of those murdered filed into court today for the trial of 93-year-old Groening . 
  Groening was known as 'The Bookkeeper' for his role in the camp in Nazi-occupied Poland . 
  He was tasked with meeting the trains bringing victims there and robbing them of their possessions . 
  Prosecutors say he was on duty when 450,000 Hungarian Jews were gassed at the camp . 
  He has never denied being at Auschwitz but denies complicity in murders . 
 